If the issue is caused by the exception thrown by RpcClientImpl::getChannel(). The only chance is that the system run out of memory or fail to create thread.  In either case, you will see error message "RpcClient failed to create a channel to" in HAWQ log. 

Please refer the code in RpcClientImpl::getChannel()

```
try {
   ...

    rc->addRef();

    if (!cleaning) {
        cleaning = true;

        if (cleaner.joinable()) {
            cleaner.join();
        }

        CREATE_THREAD(cleaner, bind(&RpcClientImpl::clean, this));
    }
} catch ...
```

Isn't it much easier to fix this issue by moving `rc->addRef();` to the end of the `try` block?
